---
description: Never mention Cursor, AI, or assistants in commits or code comments
alwaysApply: true
---

# No AI / Cursor branding in commits

- **NEVER** include references to Cursor, AI assistants, or any tool that generated the code in commit messages, commit bodies, PR titles, or PR descriptions.
- Forbidden phrases (any language): "feito pelo Cursor", "generated by Cursor", "made by AI", "co-authored by AI", "Cursor assisted", "AI-generated", "created with Cursor", or any variation.
- Write commit messages as if **you are the developer** — focus on *what* changed and *why*, not *how* it was produced.
- The same rule applies to code comments: never add comments like `// generated by Cursor` or `// AI-assisted`.
